.git
.github
.next
node_modules
.DS_Store
*.log

# Every env variant — keep the broad glob so `.env.production`,
# `.env.preview`, etc. never leak. `infra/.env.example` is already
# covered by the `infra/` rule below. The `**/` prefix is load-bearing:
# without it the pattern only matched root-level `.env*` and the
# committed `apps/web/.env` (localhost values) was reaching the prod
# image, where Next inlined `NEXT_PUBLIC_CORE_URL=http://localhost:3000`
# into the browser bundle. With the .env excluded, brand's fallback
# `https://core.${BRAND_DOMAIN}` is the single source of truth for prod.
**/.env*

# Infra & docs não vão para a imagem da app — EXCEPT the
# infra-pg-backup Go source which IS the build context for that
# image (built from the repo root). The menu Dockerfile doesn't COPY
# infra/ so re-including this path is harmless there.
#
# Docker requires every parent dir to be re-included explicitly.
infra/
!infra/iac
!infra/iac/cmd
!infra/iac/cmd/infra-pg-backup
docs/
tests/
playwright-report/
test-results/

# Test sources scattered under src/. Standalone output tracing already
# strips them at build time, but excluding them keeps the build context
# smaller and the COPY faster.
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx

# IDE / Claude
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/

# TypeScript incremental build output
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/tsconfig.tests.json

# Test coverage
coverage/

# Database backups — never allowed in image context. Even gpg-encrypted
# dumps leak volume + schedule metadata from the filenames.
*.dump
*.dump.gpg
*.sql.gz
*.bak

# Go build artefacts from `go build ./...` at the repo root. Each binary
# is 5-15 MB; they inflate the build context but are never used by the
# Node.js image.
/bws-sync
/bws-upsert
/iedora
/infra-pg-backup
# bin/dev-stack — bash script, no binary
/menu-db-migrations
/openobserve-dashboards
/state-bucket-bootstrap

# Playwright — browser binaries + merge artefacts + auth state
playwright/.cache/
blob-report/
playwright/.auth/
.playwright-mcp/

# Vitest runner cache
.vitest-cache/

# Local reference checkouts
services-references/

# Build output
dist/
